channel.title: [6-16-2014] How to setup RS3, RS2 and RS1 Server in Eclipse IDE Part 1
channel.description:
[center][size=18pt]Hello and welcome to the Amvoverwizzle Guide[/size][/center] [center][URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/22222_zps8b736c69.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/22222_zps8b736c69.png[/img][/URL][/center] [center]This Guide has tooken me hour's to perfect so please read and follow every direction you see below but first I will tell you about this guide.[/center]
[size=14pt]What is this guide about:[/size] Says it in the title but it will help you make/ setup a Runescape Evolution of combat server, Runescape Server 2, and a Runescape Classic Server.
[size=14pt]How Long did this Guide take you to make:[/size] It took me multiple hour's to do because I want this guide to be the best one out there were it simple for you to follow with out confusion.
[size=14pt]What will I need:[/size] You will need Eclipse if you are going run a RS3 Server and to not lag with choppy fps.
[center][size=14pt]Other Tutorials[/size]: [6-17-2014] [803] How to fix RS3 Weapon Icons - https://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,662947.0.html
[6-18-2014] [803] How to spawn Items/ Objects - https://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,662949.0.html
[6-19-2014] [809] How to Run latest cache in Server - https://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,663007.0.html [/center]
[center][size=14pt]Lets begin![/size][/center]
[size=14pt]Step 1:[/size] You will need to make a new folder on your desktop. Right Click your desktop and click new folder. This folder is going to hold your server.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/1_zpsd6f6f5fe.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/1_zpsd6f6f5fe.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 2:[/size] Next you are going to rename the folder that you just created to your server name that you want.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/2_zpsc6ca58cc.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/2_zpsc6ca58cc.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 3:[/size] Now to get started on making a server, you will first need to download a server. So go to Google and type Moparscape and now you will see a few things that pop up under Morparscape.org. Were it says Server Downloads you are going want to go there to find a client you want. But in this case we are making a RS3 Server so follow what I do in this guide.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/3_zps0f5ed36b.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/3_zps0f5ed36b.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 4:[/size] When your in server downloads you can search for [size=12pt][803] Virtue Final[/size] or click the following link that will take you there.
[center][size=12pt]Link:[/size] https://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,662768.0.html[/center]
You are going want to download 2 things witch will be the Client and Cache. Download the latest Client version witch is 3 from the time this guide was posted. And then download the Cache below the Version 3.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/s_zpsa8850d23.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/s_zpsa8850d23.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 5:[/size] Once you have downloaded the Client and Cache you are going want to Extract them. To Extract you will need Winrar, 7zip or any thing that will extract the folders.
[center][size=12pt]Link[/size]: http://www.rarlab.com/ [size=12pt]Link[/size]: http://www.7-zip.org/[/center]
To Extract these files what you do is right click the Archive witch is the folder you downloded and click Extract to RuneLove 3 and the other one Extract to 803_Cache.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/5_zpsbeeacda0.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/5_zpsbeeacda0.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 6:[/size] Once they have been extracted you are going to open Your server folder that you made at Step 2.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/6_zps2613ee77.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/6_zps2613ee77.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 7:[/size] You are going to Drag and drop or Copy and Paste RuneLove 3, 803_Cache Archives and the 803_Cache Folder and place them into your server Folder. And then you are going to open Runelove 3 Folder on your desktop.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/7_zps2e73bb0b.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/7_zps2e73bb0b.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 8:[/size] At this point you should have 3 things in your server folder. 2 Archives called Runelove 3, 803_Cache, and a folder called 803_cache. What you are going to do now is drag and drop or copy and paste over VirtuPk 803 and 803 Client to your server folder.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/8_zps985594e1.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/8_zps985594e1.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 9:[/size] Now you are going to rename VirtuePk 803 and name it Server.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/9_zpsdb080427.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/9_zpsdb080427.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 10:[/size] Once you have renamed VirtuePk 803 to Server, your server folder will look like this. If it does not look like this Please go back and reread the steps.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/10_zpsd72ff361.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/10_zpsd72ff361.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 11:[/size] Now we are going to rename 803 Client and call it Client.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/11_zpsf3d1873c.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/11_zpsf3d1873c.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 12:[/size] Now your server Folder should look like this. If it does not then please go back and follow the steps.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/12_zps88e8705c.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/12_zps88e8705c.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 13:[/size] Next we are going to Copy the Cache inside the folder called 803_Cache. To get here all you have to do is go into the folder called 803_cache and then open 803. Now you should be here with the many files. Make sure you high light everything by hold the left mouse button and going to the very bottom. Or Hit [size=12pt]Ctrl + A[/size] and then [size=12pt]Ctrl + C[/size] to copy.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/13_zpsa5730baa.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/13_zpsa5730baa.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 14:[/size] Now head back to the the Server Folder, and go into Server, Once your in server go into data. Once your in data you are going to create a new Folder. You are going to name this folder cache with lower cases only.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/14_zpsc3d3463c.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/14_zpsc3d3463c.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 15:[/size] Once you have renamed the folder to cache the folder will look like this.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/15_zps0851a8d5.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/15_zps0851a8d5.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 16:[/size] Now open the folder you just created witch should be cache. Now right click and paste your copied files from step 13. Or press on the Keyboard [size=12pt]Ctrl + V[/size] to paste it in.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/16_zps7c9fa063.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/16_zps7c9fa063.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 17:[/size] Your cache Folder should look like this.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/17_zps1864c042.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/17_zps1864c042.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 18:[/size] Now go to your server folder and create a new folder called Eclipse.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/18_zps9e5c8bd6.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/18_zps9e5c8bd6.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 19:[/size] Your server Folder will look like this if you did everything right.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/19_zpsb0a07a1e.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/19_zpsb0a07a1e.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 20:[/size] If you do not already have eclipse you are going want to go to google and search Eclipse and download eclipse IDE or go to the link that is listed and download eclipse standard.
[center][size=12pt]Link:[/size] http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/packages/release/kepler/sr2[/center]
Once you have eclipse you are going to extract the folder and open the folder. Inside the folder will be a Icon that looks like this. Right click it and create a shortcut but sending it to your desktop. Or just open the program from there.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/20_zpsa45bcbd1.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/20_zpsa45bcbd1.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 21:[/size] When you have opened the program you are going have a thing that will popup before you go into the actual program. Click Browse and find the server folder that you made on the desktop. Click the Server Folder and then inside there will be a folder called Eclipse. Click Eclipse folder and then press OK.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/21_zps3ce0490f.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/21_zps3ce0490f.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 22:[/size] Once you are inside eclipse there might be a thing that will popup with options. At the top left there will be a close button/ Exit. Exit the thing that is up and then you will get this. Once your here you are going want to click the arrow that is pointing downwards under File.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/22_zpsd3e91a36.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/22_zpsd3e91a36.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 23:[/size] If you did this correctly you will get this. Hover your mouse over Other... and click it.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/23_zps3a7af74e.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/23_zps3a7af74e.png[/img][/URL]
[size=14pt]Step 24:[/size] This will popup. Click Java Project and then Click Next.
[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/24_zpsa72d05e8.png.html][IMG]http://i1217.photobucket.com/albums/dd390/amvoverwizzle/RS3%20Tutorial/24_zpsa72d05e8.png[/img][/URL]
[size=24pt]Part 2 Link:[/size] https://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,662913.0.html

Once you have downloaded the Client and Cache you are going want to Extract them. To Extract you will need Winrar, 7zip or any thing that will extract the folders.

[center][size=12pt]Link[/size]: http://www.rarlab.com/
[size=12pt]Link[/size]: http://www.7-zip.org/[/center]

To Extract these files what you do is right click the Archive witch is the folder you downloded and click Extract to RuneLove 3 and the other one Extract to 803_Cache.

[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/5_zpsbeeacda0.png.html][/URL]

[size=14pt]Step 6:[/size]
Once they have been extracted you are going to open Your server folder that you made at Step 2.

[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/6_zps2613ee77.png.html][/URL]

[size=14pt]Step 7:[/size]
You are going to Drag and drop or Copy and Paste RuneLove 3, 803_Cache Archives and the 803_Cache Folder and place them into your server Folder. And then you are going to open Runelove 3 Folder on your desktop.

[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/7_zps2e73bb0b.png.html][/URL]

[size=14pt]Step 8:[/size]
At this point you should have 3 things in your server folder. 2 Archives called Runelove 3, 803_Cache, and a folder called 803_cache. What you are going to do now is drag and drop or copy and paste over VirtuPk 803 and 803 Client to your server folder.

[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/8_zps985594e1.png.html][/URL]

[size=14pt]Step 9:[/size]
Now you are going to rename VirtuePk 803 and name it Server.

[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/9_zpsdb080427.png.html][/URL]

[size=14pt]Step 10:[/size]
Once you have renamed VirtuePk 803 to Server, your server folder will look like this. If it does not look like this Please go back and reread the steps.

[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/10_zpsd72ff361.png.html][/URL]

[size=14pt]Step 11:[/size]
Now we are going to rename 803 Client and call it Client.

[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/11_zpsf3d1873c.png.html][/URL]

[size=14pt]Step 12:[/size]
Now your server Folder should look like this. If it does not then please go back and follow the steps.

[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/12_zps88e8705c.png.html][/URL]

[size=14pt]Step 13:[/size]
Next we are going to Copy the Cache inside the folder called 803_Cache. To get here all you have to do is go into the folder called 803_cache and then open 803. Now you should be here with the many files. Make sure you high light everything by hold the left mouse button and going to the very bottom. Or Hit [size=12pt]Ctrl + A[/size] and then [size=12pt]Ctrl + C[/size] to copy.

[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/13_zpsa5730baa.png.html][/URL]

[size=14pt]Step 14:[/size]
Now head back to the the Server Folder, and go into Server, Once your in server go into data. Once your in data you are going to create a new Folder. You are going to name this folder cache with lower cases only.

[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/14_zpsc3d3463c.png.html][/URL]

[size=14pt]Step 15:[/size]
Once you have renamed the folder to cache the folder will look like this.

[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/15_zps0851a8d5.png.html][/URL]

[size=14pt]Step 16:[/size]
Now open the folder you just created witch should be cache. Now right click and paste your copied files from step 13. Or press on the Keyboard [size=12pt]Ctrl + V[/size] to paste it in.

[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/16_zps7c9fa063.png.html][/URL]

[size=14pt]Step 17:[/size]
Your cache Folder should look like this.

[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/17_zps1864c042.png.html][/URL]

[size=14pt]Step 18:[/size]
Now go to your server folder and create a new folder called Eclipse.

[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/18_zps9e5c8bd6.png.html][/URL]

[size=14pt]Step 19:[/size]
Your server Folder will look like this if you did everything right.

[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/19_zpsb0a07a1e.png.html][/URL]

[size=14pt]Step 20:[/size]
If you do not already have eclipse you are going want to go to google and search Eclipse and download eclipse IDE or go to the link that is listed and download eclipse standard.

[center][size=12pt]Link:[/size] http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/packages/release/kepler/sr2[/center]

Once you have eclipse you are going to extract the folder and open the folder. Inside the folder will be a Icon that looks like this. Right click it and create a shortcut but sending it to your desktop. Or just open the program from there.

[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/20_zpsa45bcbd1.png.html][/URL]

[size=14pt]Step 21:[/size]
When you have opened the program you are going have a thing that will popup before you go into the actual program. Click Browse and find the server folder that you made on the desktop. Click the Server Folder and then inside there will be a folder called Eclipse. Click Eclipse folder and then press OK.

[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/21_zps3ce0490f.png.html][/URL]

[size=14pt]Step 22:[/size]
Once you are inside eclipse there might be a thing that will popup with options. At the top left there will be a close button/ Exit. Exit the thing that is up and then you will get this. Once your here you are going want to click the arrow that is pointing downwards under File.

[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/22_zpsd3e91a36.png.html][/URL]

[size=14pt]Step 23:[/size]
If you did this correctly you will get this. Hover your mouse over Other… and click it.

[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/23_zps3a7af74e.png.html][/URL]

[size=14pt]Step 24:[/size]
This will popup. Click Java Project and then Click Next.

[URL=http://s1217.photobucket.com/user/amvoverwizzle/media/RS3%20Tutorial/24_zpsa72d05e8.png.html][/URL]
